<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>In writing, Wolfe clearly has a lot to say and he often seems bubbling over with ideas. He wisely draws from his reading strengths, using interesting vocabulary and imagery that model books he has read. Wolfe adds a unique and engaging &ldquo;voice&rdquo; to his writing; however, his organization can be a bit loose and scattered, and he could afford to pay more attenti;reader_notes=;notes=;status=1;submit=Save Section;

